 {"id":"franken_numpy-boe","title":"Replace absolute convergence thresholds in sqrtm and logm with relative checks","description":"## Problem\n\nMatrix square root (sqrtm_nxn) and matrix logarithm (logm_nxn) use absolute convergence thresholds:\n\n### sqrtm_nxn (Denman-Beavers iteration)\n- Line ~2626: convergence check `1e-14` — compares max element difference between successive iterates\n- Problem: For matrices with large entries, convergence to 1e-14 absolute difference may never occur or may be meaningless. For matrices with small entries, 1e-14 is too loose.\n\n### logm_nxn\n- Line ~2666: scaling threshold `0.5` — checks ||M - I|| < 0.5 to decide when to stop scaling\n- This is actually reasonable (it's a relative-to-identity check) and standard in the algorithm\n- Line ~2693: Taylor convergence `1e-15` — absolute check on term size\n- Problem: Same scale-sensitivity issue as sqrtm\n\n## What SciPy Does\n\nSciPy's sqrtm uses Schur decomposition followed by a triangular square root (Björck-Hammarling algorithm), not Denman-Beavers. But if using iterative methods, they check relative convergence: `||Y_{k+1} - Y_k|| / ||Y_k|| < eps`.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\n### sqrtm_nxn\n1. At each iteration, compute `rel_change = max_diff / max(||Y_k||, 1.0)`\n2. Converge when `rel_change < f64::EPSILON * 100` (few ULPs of relative change)\n3. Keep SQRTM_MAX_ITERATIONS as safety cap\n\n### logm_nxn\n1. The `0.5` scaling threshold is fine (it's relative to the identity matrix)\n2. Replace `1e-15` Taylor convergence with adaptive stopping (covered by the Taylor adaptive stopping bead)\n\n## Validation\n\n- sqrtm tests must pass (especially the A = sqrtm(A)² roundtrip identity)\n- logm tests must pass\n- funm tests must pass (funm uses sqrtm and logm internally)\n- Test with both well-conditioned and poorly-scaled matrices\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n- `crates/fnp-linalg/src/lib.rs` — sqrtm_nxn convergence check","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:05:43.497459889Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T03:19:27.094989729Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T03:19:27.094304833Z","close_reason":"sqrtm convergence now relative (eps*64*||Y||), logm Taylor uses adaptive term-vs-result comparison, eigvector normalization guard uses f64::MIN_POSITIVE. All 201 tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-boe","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-z8x","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:06:49.724467210Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
